Package: SpecPP
Title: Spectral Analysis for Point Processes
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Qi-Wen", "Ding", email = "r07227101@ntu.edu.tw", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Junho", "Yang", email = "junhoyang@stat.sinica.edu.tw", role = c("aut")),
    person("Joonho", "Shin", email = "joonho.shin@sungshin.ac.kr", role = c("aut")))
Description: An R package for spectral analysis of multivariate spatial point 
    patterns in a rectangular region. Given a multivariate point pattern and a 
    parametric model of the intensity function, this package facilitates the 
    characterization of frequency-domain features from your data through kernel 
    smoothing. It includes functions for spectral density estimation, bandwidth 
    selection, visualization, and coherence analysis.
